<font color="#FF0000">TIRED OLD REMF</font><br>
<tt>Sun Aug 17 23:40:38 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Dropping off LRRP's, SF's, Seals, etc. was one thing... picking'em up was something else.<br><br>
&quot;THE RACE&quot;<br><br>
I remember the expanse of ominous gree<br>
that spread before my eyes<br>
and the urgent pleas, from men unseen.<br>
They were desperate, ephermeral cries.<br><br>
I summoned more from the groaning ship<br>
As we plunged through the failing light.<br>
Scanning the guages, I chewed my lip<br>
and prayed for faster flight.<br><br>
&quot;Just north of a winding river...<br>
below a prominent ridge...<br>
Look for a road that is barely a sliver.<br>
We're under the rotting bridge.&quot;<br><br>
A ghostly mist in the shadows below<br>
was a joyous and wonderful sight.<br>
It marked the course of the river's flow, <br>
as dusk turned into night.<br><br>
Off to the north the bamboo juted<br>
into an indigo sky.<br>
A narrow road, twisted and rutted,<br>
soon caught my straining eye.<br><br>
&quot;We hear you, Sir!&quot; the radio sputtered,<br>
You're a click or so from the creek.&quot;<br>
Thank you, God,&quot; I quickly muttered,<br>
as sweat rolled down my cheek.<br><br>
They clamored up the muddy bank<br>
and ran down the fading road.<br>
With the Asian sun, my heart, too, sank<br>
when I saw their grisly load.<br><br>
Across each shoulder, they bore the dead,<br>
who had lived but minutes before.<br>
Gently they laid them in pools of red<br>
upon the cargo floor.<br><br>
A deep jungle darkness had settled in<br>
and enemy bullets went awry.<br>
Now, blackness had become our special friend,<br>
while tracers searched the sky.<br><br>
True, I had won the race with nightfall<br>
and had found their hiding place,<br>
But a darker specter heard the call<br>
and had matched my frantic pace.<br><br>
Once aloft, I hung my head<br>
as the jungle spead past below.<br>
&quot;Could I have spared those, now dead,<br>
...had I not been so slow?&quot;<br><br>
No one could hear me weeping<br>
above the engine's roar,<br>
for those sprawled as if sleeping,<br>
upon my cargo floor.<br><br>
Then came a voice from far away,<br>
&quot;They're with me... I'll comfort their mothers.<br>
Tomorrow, I'll give you another day,<br>
and I'll help you rescue others.&quot;<br><br>
From &quot;Scars and Stripes, Forever,&quot; copywrite 1990 E. Ramon
